<top>
<num> Number: 3401052-3
<title> One notable research direction in QR, which is also applicable for e-commerce, focuses on increasing the recall. This direction is especially important for null queries that yield no results. Alternative queries are generated by dropping [4, 24, 28, 46, 47] or substituting [7, 16, 25] tokens from the original query.

<desc> Description:

<narr> Narrative:

</top>

<top>
<num> Number: 3401052-4
<title> Other ideas for substitution-based solutions, using the query-flow graph [6], were also proposed [7, 16]. However, finding good recommendations for tail e-commerce queries based on session co-occurrence turns to be difficult [16].

<desc> Description:

<narr> Narrative:

