<title> A fundamental task in voice shopping is product recommendation, where the goal is to recommend relevant products to customers by inferring their preferences. While a growing body of research has addressed the voice-based recommendation problem from the dialogue perspective, i.e., improving the effectiveness of question-answering between the customer and system [7, 8, 11, 23, 25, 44, 45], relatively little work has been focused on addressing the specific challenges arising in recommendation on Voice [40].

