<title> Neural network-based methods are more capable of learning non-linear latent representations for users and items and potentially also their interactions (see a recent survey [46]). Specific to neural transfer learning for cross-domain recommendation, [14] introduce a multi-view deep learning method that learns shared user representations from user-item interactions in different domains. [26] propose to incorporate content information into the multi-view neural network.

