<title> In Web-based information systems, repeated item consumption has been shown to be most affected by the recency and quality of the item, with recency being more critical [1]. [4] study such a behavior in more detail and reveals the increasing inter-arrival gaps of repeated item consumption that eventually lead to abandonment. In online shopping, [5] study repeated purchases for consumable products, e.g., toothpaste and diapers, and propose a prediction model that helps increase the product click-through rate.

